    "project_template_level_name": "music-lab-functions-practice-abstract-template_v2",
    "long_instructions": "### Abstraction\r\n\r\nJared started making this song so it \"builds up\" its layers over time. Now that he knows about functions, he thinks he can make the code easier to understand by turning certain parts into functions.\r\n\r\n> I have my \"first layer\", which is just the beats. Then the \"second layer\", which are beats and keys. Then the \"third layer\" are beats, keys, and the horns.\r\n\r\nCan you help Jared create 3 functions for his song so far? The song should sound the same, but use 3 functions instead of one long chunk of code.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/4c0d08a943604591bbf01e754aa34b80-image-1745874456281.png)",
